parameters: I gotta finish up here first...
Leave me alone ya little brat, I'm trynna get a pop.
C'mon ya piece a crap - gimme the pop!
You again? I thought I told you th-
From now on YOU will be pulling that overfed weight of
yours around here, and show Sifa some goddamn respect.
You’re afraid of Sifa, terrified even, like she’s your
superior and you want nothing more than to make her feel
happy while working here. Is that understood, fatass?
Yes... I... Wh-What happened? What was I doing again?
You decided to get off your break early
to go help Sifa with that mess, remember?
Ah... Right. I was. Excuse me, sir...
There you are! Hey, did you...
Did you say anything to Roger?
Hmmm, nope! I was keeping my distance,
seemed like he was in a bad mood.
Actually I don’t think he’s that bad. He just walked over
to take care of that mess, and even offered me a raise!
Though it is sort of surprising.
It shouldn’t be a surprise at all, Sifa. You work hard,
be it here or at school, and try to make everyone happy.
It’s about time someone remembered that, especially you.
Aww... You’re right, \N[001]. I tend to put
other people’s needs above my own at times.
But that’s kind of why I like working here, because I get
to help people with little things that can make a bigger
impact, even if I don’t personally see it myself.
But enough about me, what can I help you with today?
Heh... I almost forgot why I came in here myself.
You wouldn’t happen to have any heavy duty bleach for sale,
would you? The stronger the better.
*Giggle* You’re not planning on murdering anyone, are you?
One sec, I know just the thing, meet me at the register.
<Man, Sifa really does go above and beyond for people.
I should try and hang out with her more at some point.
But first things first, laundry day.>
This should do the trick! Though I should warn you,
Use too much and you might ruin sensitive materials.
We wouldn’t want that now, would we? So what do I owe you?
Normally it’d be $10 but for you, let’s say
we use my employee discount. Half off.
Nah, it’s fine. I’m sure Roger won’t notice.
If you really insist, sure, I’ll take you up on that offer.
Thanks, Sifa. You have no idea how much you’ve made my day.
Anytime! Thanks for shopping with us, \N[001].
Count on it. I’ll see you at school.
<Now it’s time for a little housework. I better run home
and start the washer before Mom gets off work.>
Oh, I- I don't have that much...
Oh, really? Well, I mean, I can't really give it away...
Can you get the $5 and come back?
Oh! E-excuse me, sir - I was just getting back to work!
Excuse me, Miss? Do you work here?
Sifa? I didn’t know you worked here. Sorry, didn’t mean
to scare you there, I was just looking for someone
to help me with some shopping.
Aw man... This is totally my fault.
I can pay for it, honest.
That’s alright, \N[001], accidents happen, and it’s
technically my fault. I couldn’t find the step ladder,
and I’m being pulled every which way today.
We’re a little short staffed at the moment.
Are you? Because I’ve been meaning to look
for a job to earn some extra ca-
I wanna go on my lunch break already.
N-No, Roger. I got tied up helping a customer, and there’s
not enough people covering the front registers.
B-But I’ll get to it, I promise!
You break this? Because you sure as hell bought it.
Wait! That... That was my fault too...
Of course it was. I’ll have to dock your pay, Smyth.
There’s a bucket and washcloth over there for you to
clean this up. Do you think you can handle THAT?
... Yes, Roger. I’ll take care of it immediately.
Hey watch the tone, asshole. She didn’t do anything wrong.
And who the hell are you, punk?! I can talk to my staff any
way I want, especially when they’re as worthless as her!
So as I was saying, Smyth, go be useful for a
change and go clean up this mess! I’m on break. And you...
Buy something, or get out before I call
the cops and report you for loitering.
You shouldn’t let him talk to you like that, Sifa.
*Sigh* Not much I can do, he’s my boss.
But it was sweet of you to try and stick up for me.
Just hang back, stay out of Roger’s sight, and after I’m
done here I’ll come help you with what you need. Deal?
<That prick! Well now I’m not leaving until
I get the bleach AND teach that guy a lesson.>
Oh, what a mess I made...
Hey, I got the cash - you serious, Sifa?
You wouldn’t get in trouble for the discount,
Nah, it’s fine. I’m sure Roger won’t notice.
If you really insist, sure, I’ll take you up on that offer.
Thanks, Sifa. You have no idea how much you’ve made my day.
Anytime! Thanks for shopping with us, \N[001].
Count on it. I’ll see you at school.
<Now it’s time for a little housework. I better run home
and start the washer before Mom gets off work.>
Oh, I- I don't have that much...
Oh, really? Well, I mean, I can't really give it away...
Can you get the $5 and come back?
Hi, I'm pretty busy right now but we should talk later!
<I can’t be here all day looking around, Mom will be home
soon. Maybe there’s a clerk who can help me...>
Oh, heya kiddo! I'm just grabbing a few things for dinner
but I'll catch up with you at home, okay?
Huh. Looks like it's pretty high up there...
Yeah, I don't think I'll be able to reach it.
I'll try and find the manager, maybe they have a stool
or one of those little grabby things...
I could always just give you a boost. It'd be a lot faster,
and we wouldn't have to deal with the manager. I don't know
if you've met him, but he's kind of a jerk.
Hm... I do remember him being rather... Crude.
Okay, \N[001]. Just do it quickly, I don't want anyone
seeing and thinking up something crazy about us...
<I can feel his breath on me...>
<Oh, my! His face is buried in my cleavage - I can't
believe how sensitive my boobs have gotten!>
Yep! You did so well today!
Huh. Looks like it's pretty high up there...
Yeah, I don't think I'll be able to reach it.
I'll try and find the manager, maybe they have a stool
or one of those little grabby things...
I could always just give you a boost. It'd be a lot faster,
and we wouldn't have to deal with the manager. I don't know
if you've met him, but he's kind of a jerk.
Hm... I do remember him being rather... Crude.
Okay, \N[001]. Just do it quickly, I don't want anyone
seeing and thinking up something crazy about us...
<I can feel his breath on me...>
<Oh, my! His face is buried in my cleavage - I can't
believe how sensitive my boobs have gotten!>
Yep! You did so well today!
This is new... Cool, little prepackaged dinner and wine
kits - Steak with mashed potatoes and mixed vegetables,
salmon with wild rice, oh! Chicken stir-fry!
Mom showed me how to make that, I could
probably figure this one out on my own!
Shoot, $50? I'll need to come back when I have enough money.
I need to get the $50 for this...
Alright, I got enough cash now, I should take this
to the counter and pay for it.
Hey, need to pay for this stuff.
I don't need to buy milk, but I'm suddenly very thirsty...
